This paper focuses on adapting a parser to a specific sublanguage (biomedical), which is a common task in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of different approaches to handling unknown words, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.IR). Additionally, the use of a domain-specific part-of-speech tagger involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the study of a specific sublanguage (biomedical) could also be relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY), which deals with communication and control in complex systems.
